Red margin bamboo is exceptionally cold hardy and can survive freezing winter temperatures.
Agricultural runoff pollutes local rivers, severely impacting freshwater fish and amphibian species. Implementing buffer zones of native vegetation along waterways can filter harmful chemicals before they reach habitats.
